<div id="review_2637550777" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2637550777" />
    <a title="Cole Trent" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/90964687-cole-trent"><img alt="Cole Trent" src="https://s.gr-assets.com/assets/nophoto/user/m_50x66-82093808bca726cb3249a493fbd3bd0f.png" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2637550777?book_show_action=true">Jan 30, 2019</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Cole Trent" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Cole Trent" href="/user/show/90964687-cole-trent">Cole Trent</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="kindle " href="/book/show/6135744-two-treatises-of-government">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2637550777" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer12385077827768900977"><strong>Great read with a deep modern relevance.</strong><br/><br/> John Locke has an eloquent way of explaining things that that we inhabitants of modern day western society seem to take for granted. You may read these books and think to yourself &quot;How stupidly obvious! Why is he going to such great lengths to explain things which are so commonly known?&quot; but soon you begin to understand that, in the days of the enlightenment, a time of monarchies and auto-da-fés, putting forth such liberal ideas was truly ground breaking.</span>
  <span id="freeText12385077827768900977" style="display:none"><strong>Great read with a deep modern relevance.</strong><br /><br /> John Locke has an eloquent way of explaining things that that we inhabitants of modern day western society seem to take for granted. You may read these books and think to yourself "How stupidly obvious! Why is he going to such great lengths to explain things which are so commonly known?" but soon you begin to understand that, in the days of the enlightenment, a time of monarchies and auto-da-fés, putting forth such liberal ideas was truly ground breaking. This is a very important work which helped to shape western civilization as we know it today.</span>
  <a data-text-id="12385077827768900977" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


